  "text": "in Figure 9 (b) are 1.0-3.0 M low-mass pre-mainsequence sources in RCW 49 for the following reasons. Their K s -band brightness (13-16 mag) is consistent with the NIR brightness of pre-main-sequence sources in this mass range. Their hard-band X-ray luminosities 10 30 -10 31.5 ergs s −1 and flaring are typical of this class of stars in near-by regions (e.g., Wolk et al. 2006; Getman et al. 2006) . The ratio of X-ray to NIR brightness of 10 −1 -10 −3 is consistent with the fractional X-ray to bolometric luminosity of 10 −3 -10 −5 common among these sources. The K s -band bolometric corrections for A0 V, F0 V, and G0 V stars are -3.75, -2.85, and -2.25 mag [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
